^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-09 19:37] observe — Existing PWA wiring is present across the site, but the worker is registered from `/public/sw.js`, which limits scope to `/public/*` on static hosting.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:37] observe — The current precache list uses route forms like `/about/index.html`, while the site navigates with mixed `/about` and `/topics/software/` URLs.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:37] observe — `manifest.webmanifest` references icon and screenshot assets that are not present under `public/images`.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:37] decide — Improve the PWA shell with a root-scoped worker, real install assets, contextual install/update prompts, and a dedicated offline page.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:37] taste — Favor trust and containment: only promise install/offline/update behavior the static shell can actually honor.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:44] implement — Added a canonical root `sw.js`, kept `/public/sw.js` as a compatibility wrapper, and switched the shell logic to navigation-aware caching with an explicit offline route.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:45] implement — Replaced manifest version polling with service-worker lifecycle handling, contextual install prompts, and generated install icon assets from existing site artwork.
 >>[2026-04-09 19:51] verify — `node --check` passed for `sw.js` and `public/js/pwa-update-handler.js`; `python3 -m json.tool manifest.webmanifest` passed; generated icons match declared sizes; local static-server HEAD checks returned `200` for `/sw.js`, `/manifest.webmanifest`, `/offline/`, `/public/images/icon-192.png`, `/about/`, and `301` for `/about`.
}

